Pac-Man
1.	The game must show a maze with paths and walls
2.	There must be pellets that can be collected
3.	The pellets must disappear when collected
4.	There must be ghosts that can be eaten
5.	There can be a tracked score
6.	The score must be based on pellets collected and ghosts eaten
7.	The game must detect when the player hits an enemy
8.	The player’s lives must decrease when he/she hits an enemy
9.	The game must end when the player is out of lives
10.	The game can display a final score

Tetris
1.	The game must show a vertical screen
2.	The game must drop blocks down the screen
3.	The player must be able to adjust the blocks before they get to the bottom
4.	The game must lock a block into place when it cannot move down anymore
5.	The game must detect fully filled horizontal lines
6.	Fully filled horizontal lines must be removed
7.	All blocks above cleared lines must move down
8.	The difficulty can continue to increase as the game continues
9.	The game can track the player’s score
10.	The game must end when blocks cannot be dropped anymore

Snake
1.	The game must show a rectangular field
2.	The player must be able to move around as a continuously moving “snake”
3.	The player must be able to guide the snake
4.	There must be randomly spawning apples in the field
5.	The apples can spawn on any coordinate held by the player
6.	Once the player moves over an apple, the length of the snake must grow
7.	The game must end if the player collides with himself/herself or the edge of the field
8.	As the game continues, the field size must remain the same
9.	The player’s score must increase with each apple consumed
10.	The player’s high score can be tracked for future attempts.

